President Cyril Ramaphosa paid tribute to SANDF members during Armed Forces Day. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - SANDF Commander-in-Chief President Cyril Ramaphosa has praised army personnel for the work carried out during the Covid-19 pandemic. He was speaking at the commemoration of Armed Forces Day in Mpumalanga. Ramaphosa says members of the SANDF served the country with distinction under difficult conditions. "It is now two years since the start of Covid-19, SANDF was there assisting with implementation and maintenance of national state of disaster in the early weeks and months of the pandemic," he said.